# Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to verify Red Hat container images using Sigstore infrastructure.
It covers verification via Cosign, Skopeo, Podman, Buildah, oc-mirror v2, OpenShift ImagePolicy (Tech Preview), and Red Hat ACS.

There is no application source code — the repo consists of YAML/JSON configs, shell scripts, sample Dockerfiles, GitHub Actions workflows, and documentation.

# Assumed Role

You are a senior engineer with expertise in:
- OpenShift/Kubernetes
- Sigstore (Cosign, Fulcio, Rekor) and container image signing/verification
- Bash scripting
- YAML and JSON configuration
- GitHub Actions CI/CD
